text.tspan: 3rd Workshop on Python in High Energy Physics
PyHEP is a series of workshops initiated and supported by the HEP Software Foundation (HSF)
to discuss and promote the use of Python in the HEP community.
PyHEP 2020 will be held on the University of Texas at Austin campus, right next door to SciPy 2020,
the primary conference for the scientific Python community at large. SciPy 2020 will be held on
July 6‒12, making it easy to attend both.
Matthew Feickert — University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign
Peter Onyisi — The University of Texas at Austin
